pageContext.claim: “Number two, a positive note, we're doing very well on trade, we're doing very well — our companies are very strong. Don’t forget, we're still up from when I came in, 38 percent or something. You know, it’s a tremendous — it’s not like we're up — and we’re much stronger.”
pageContext.analysis: The Dow Jones industrial average was 25 percent higher than Jan. 20, 2017, when he took the oath of office; the Standard & Poor’s 500-stock index was up about 18 percent. Trump tends to date things from the election, in effect wiping out the last three months of Barack Obama’s term. But even that would not explain his use of 38 percent.
